## IV Conclusion

We have experimentally demonstrated the high-performance lateral GaN SBDs with the W anode. Even with a fully recessed AlGaN barrier at the anode region, a low V\({}_{\text{on}}\) of 0.35 V with an ultrahigh uniformity has been achieved due to the low work function of W, which can still provide enough barrier height for the reverse leakage current blocking. A high power FOM of \(1.7\times 10^{3}\) MW/cm\({}^{2}\) with BV = 1.1 kV and differential R\({}_{\text{on},\text{sp}}\) = 0.72 m\(\Omega\)-cm\({}^{2}\) is achieved at an L\({}_{\text{AC}}\) = 10 \(\mu\)m. Meanwhile, a high BV of 1.9 kV is demonstrated with a power FOM of \(1.4\times 10^{3}\) MW/cm\({}^{2}\) and a differential R\({}_{\text{on},\text{sp}}\) of 2.61 m\(\Omega\)-cm\({}^{2}\) at an L\({}_{\text{AC}}\) = 25 \(\mu\)m. The lateral GaN SBDs with the W anode, high V\({}_{\text{on}}\) uniformity, high current on/off ratio, high BV, high power FOM and low R\({}_{\text{on},\text{sp}}\), thus demonstrating their great potential as future high-performance power rectifiers.

